@orrdavid @Mr_Neutral_Man I think you are definining leverage differently.

Suppose I own JPM. There is a LOT of leverage working for me in the bank - but I do not necessarily think of myself as levered because I DO NOT GUARANTEE THE DEBT.

Berkshire is like that. The parent company is deeply unlevered.

@SowingAlphaSeed I think consolidated leverage is different from nonconsolidated leverage. 

But yes - organising non-recourse finance is kind of a cute way of getting benefits but not all the pain of leverage.

You usually pay for it though.

